Preheat your #oven{} to 220°C/200°C fan/gas mark 7.

Pour the @Water for the Rice{200%ml} into a #medium saucepan{} with a tight-fitting
#lid{}.

Stir in the @Basmati Rice{100%g} and @salt{1/4%tsp} and bring to the boil. Once
boiling, turn the heat down to medium and cover with the lid.

Leave to cook for ~{10%mins}, then remove the pan from the heat (still covered)
and leave to the side for another ~{10%mins} or until ready to serve (the rice
will continue to cook in its own steam).

Meanwhile, peel and grate the @Garlic Clove{1} (or use a #garlic press{}).

Break up the @Unconventional Plant-Based Burgers{2} into a #large bowl{} and
combine with the garlic.

Using your hands, mix together well with the @Breadcrumbs{10%g} and
@Curry Powder Mix{1%sachet}.

Shape into balls, 2 per person.

Place the plant-based meatballs onto a lined #baking tray{} and bake on the
middle shelf of your oven until browned on the outside, ~{12-14%mins}.

> IMPORTANT: Ensure they're piping hot throughout.

Meanwhile, trim the @Courgette{1}, then quarter lengthways. Chop widthways into
1cm chunks.

Heat a drizzle of @oil{} in a #large frying pan{} on high heat. When hot, add
the courgette and cook until charred, ~{6-8%mins} total. Turn only every
couple of mins.

Once cooked, season with @salt{} and @pepper{}, then transfer the courgette to a
#bowl{} and cover to keep warm.

Pop the (now empty) pan back on medium heat with another drizzle of @oil{}. Add
the @Tomato Puree{30%g}, @Korma Curry Paste{50%g}, then fry for ~{30%secs}.

Stir in the @Vegetable Stock Paste{10%g}, @Water for the Sauce{200%ml} and a
pinch of @sugar{pinch} (if you have any). Bring to the boil, then lower the heat
and simmer until thickened, ~{4-5%mins}.

Once the sauce has thickened, add the @Baby Spinach{40%g} to the pan a handful at
a time until wilted and piping hot, ~{1-2%mins}. Remove from the heat.

When the plant-based meatballs are ready, gently stir them into the curry sauce
along with the charred courgette. Taste and season with @salt{} and @pepper{} if
needed.

Share the rice between your #serving bowls{} and spoon over the curry to finish.

Enjoy!